items.name: Ext.form.action.DirectSubmit
clientValidation
items.text:
Determines whether a Form's fields are validated in a final call to {@link Ext.form.Basic#method!isValid Ext.form.Basic#isValid} prior
to submission. Pass false in the Form's submit options to prevent this.

items.name: failure
items.text:
The function to call when a failure packet was received, or when an error
occurred in the Ajax communication.

items.name: form
items.text: The form that requested the action

items.name: action
form
items.text: The {@link Ext.form.Basic} instance that is invoking this Action. Required.

items.name: headers
items.text:
Extra headers to be sent in the AJAX request for submit and load actions.
See {@link Ext.data.proxy.Ajax#cfg!headers Ext.data.proxy.Ajax#headers}.

**Note:** Headers are not sent during file upload.

items.name: method
items.text:
The HTTP method to use to access the requested URL.
Defaults to the {@link Ext.form.Basic#cfg!method Ext.form.Basic#method}, or 'POST' if not specified.

items.name: params
items.text:
Extra parameter values to pass. These are added to the Form's {@link Ext.form.Basic#cfg!baseParams Ext.form.Basic#baseParams} and passed to the
specified URL along with the Form's input fields.

Parameters are encoded as standard HTTP parameters using {@link Ext#method!urlEncode Ext#urlEncode}.

items.name: reset
items.text:
When set to **true**, causes the Form to be {@link Ext.form.Basic#method!reset Ext.form.Basic#reset} on Action success. If specified,
this happens before the {@link #cfg!success #success} callback is called and before the Form's
{@link Ext.form.Basic#event!actioncomplete Ext.form.Basic#actioncomplete} event fires.

items.name: scope
items.text:
The scope in which to call the configured #success and #failure callback functions
(the `this` reference for the callback functions).

items.name: submitEmptyText
items.text: If set to true, the emptyText value will be sent with the form when it is submitted.

items.name: success
items.text: The function to call when a valid success return packet is received.

items.name: form
items.text: The form that requested the action

items.name: action
items.text:
The Action class. The {@link #property!result #result} property of this object may
be examined to perform custom post-processing.

items.name: timeout
items.text:
The number of seconds to wait for a server response before failing with the {@link #property!failureType #failureType} as
{@link Ext.form.action.Action#static-property!CONNECT_FAILURE Ext.form.action.Action#CONNECT_FAILURE}. If not specified, defaults to the configured
{@link Ext.form.Basic#cfg!timeout Ext.form.Basic#timeout} of the {@link #cfg!form #form}.

items.name: url
items.text:
The URL that the Action is to invoke. Will default to the {@link Ext.form.Basic#cfg!url Ext.form.Basic#url} configured on the
{@link #cfg!form #form}.

items.name: waitMsg
items.text:
The message to be displayed by a call to {@link Ext.window.MessageBox#method!wait Ext.window.MessageBox#wait} during the time the action is being
processed.

items.name: waitTitle
items.text:
The title to be displayed by a call to {@link Ext.window.MessageBox#method!wait Ext.window.MessageBox#wait} during the time the action is being
processed.

is typically called by the `deprecated` config.

items.name: buildForm
items.text:
Builds a form element containing fields corresponding to all the parameters to be
submitted (everything returned by {@link #method!getParams #getParams}.

NOTE: the form element is automatically added to the DOM, so any code that uses
it must remove it from the DOM after finishing with it.

items.name: statics
toLocaleString
items.text:
Returns a string representing the object. This method is meant to be overridden by derived objects
for locale-specific purposes.

`{@link Object}`'s `{@link #method!toLocaleString toLocaleString}` returns the result of calling `{@link #method!toString toString}`.

This function is provided to give objects a generic `{@link #method!toLocaleString toLocaleString}` method, even though not all
may use it. Currently, only `{@link Array}`, `{@link Number}`, and `{@link Date}` override `{@link #method!toLocaleString toLocaleString}`.
Object represented as a string.

items.name: valueOf
items.text:
Returns the primitive value of the specified object.

JavaScript calls the `{@link #method!valueOf valueOf}` method to convert an object to a primitive value. You rarely need to
invoke the `{@link #method!valueOf valueOf}` method yourself; JavaScript automatically invokes it when encountering an
object where a primitive value is expected.

By default, the `{@link #method!valueOf valueOf}` method is inherited by every object descended from `{@link Object}`. Every built-
in core object overrides this method to return an appropriate value. If an object has no primitive
value, `{@link #method!valueOf valueOf}` returns the object itself, which is displayed as:

    [object Object]

You can use `{@link #method!valueOf valueOf}` within your own code to convert a built-in object into a primitive value.
When you create a custom object, you can override `Object.valueOf` to call a custom method instead
of the default `{@link Object}` method.

You can create a function to be called in place of the default `{@link #method!valueOf valueOf}` method. Your function must
take no arguments.

Suppose you have an object type `myNumberType` and you want to create a `{@link #method!valueOf valueOf}` method for it.
The following code assigns a user-defined function to the object's valueOf method:

    myNumberType.prototype.valueOf = new Function(functionText)

With the preceding code in place, any time an object of type `myNumberType` is used in a context
where it is to be represented as a primitive value, JavaScript automatically calls the function
defined in the preceding code.

An object's `{@link #method!valueOf valueOf}` method is usually invoked by JavaScript, but you can invoke it yourself as
follows:

    myNumber.valueOf()

Note: Objects in string contexts convert via the `{@link #method!toString toString}` method, which is different from
`{@link String}` objects converting to string primitives using `{@link #method!valueOf valueOf}`. All objects have a string
conversion, if only `"[object type]"`. But many objects do not convert to number, boolean, or
function.
Returns value of the object or the object itself.

items.name: $configPrefixed
items.text:
The value `true` causes `config` values to be stored on instances using a
property name prefixed with an underscore ("_") character. A value of `false`
stores `config` values as properties using their exact name (no prefix).

items.name: $configStrict
items.text:
The value `true` instructs the `{@link #method!initConfig initConfig}` method to only honor values for
properties declared in the `config` block of a class. When `false`, properties
that are not declared in a `config` block will be placed on the instance.
